{{Quote|Who are these Coyn?"<br />"They are warriors for hire. Their entire people join their mercenary guilds and hire themselves out for various operations around the galaxy. The group who took over the ruins call themselves Razor Runners. Named after their leader, Hal Razor, no doubt.|A spacer and Pletus Croix|<ref name="SWG:ToOW">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan]]''</ref>}}
The '''Razor Runners''' were a group of [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] and bandits commanded by [[Hal Razor]] found on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Mustafar/Legends|Mustafar]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].
[[File:RazorRunnerTrooper-TOTC.jpg|thumb|left|200px|A Razor Runner trooper]]
There were four distinct classes of Razor Runners: Troopers, Commandos, Shock Troopers, and Elite Troopers. They were known to be seen near the [[Northern Jedi Ruins]] at the [[Smoking Forest/Legends|Smoking Forest]] and would often shoot down passing vehicles for sport.

==Behind the scenes==
The Razor Runners appeared in the video game Star Wars Galaxies, a massively multiplayer online role-playing game developed by Sony Online Entertainment and published by LucasArts, prior to its closure on [[December 15]], 2011.

